{"type":"message","id":"2bc688d7","parentId":"77019399","timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:40:15.833Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the sessions and identify the ACTIVE master-orchestrator sessions, excluding this cron session.\n\nCurrent time: 1776184757844 (from updatedAt of first session)\n\nActive sessions (status = running):\n1. `agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922` - running - label: \"telegram-5p-status-v5\" - runtimeMs: 39918 (~40s)\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` - running - label: \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\" - THIS IS THE CRON SESSION, exclude it\n\n\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` - running - label: \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" - runtimeMs: 117833 (~2min)\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` - running - label: \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" - runtimeMs: 32056253 (~8h 54min)\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` - running - label: \"telegram:group:-5163901258\" - runtimeMs: 3754 (~4s)\n6. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff` - running - label: \"Cron: Send this exact message to Telegram group -5163901258:\" - runtimeMs: 27955853 (~7h 46min)\n\nNow I'm checking the session history to understand what each of these is doing. For the first one, I can see it's a Telegram status report being processed by the planner subagent. For the second, it's the 5p progress report cron job that's been running for about 2 minutes, though I need to verify the exact label.\n\nLooking at the third one, the \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" has been running for over 8 hours, which seems like an unusually long runtime for a cron job. The fourth is a Telegram group session that's only been active for about 4 seconds. And the last one is another cron job sending messages to the Telegram group that's been running for nearly 8 hours.\n\nI'm wondering if that 8+ hour runtime for the DTLX cron might be a display issue or if the job genuinely started around 7:44 AM UTC this morning. I need to focus on filtering for master-orchestrator sessions specifically, excluding the cron sessions that are still running.\n\nThe active master-orchestrator sessions I should track are the 5p progress report cron, the DTLX version cron, the Telegram group session, and the message-sending cron. I'm working through the session labels to map them to their actual tasks and calculate how long they've been running based on the current timestamp. I'm looking at the detailed breakdown for each active session now. The first one is the 5p Progress Report running on webchat, started about 2 minutes ago. The second is the DTLX variant of the same report, but it's been running for nearly 9 hours since early this morning. There's also a Telegram group session and what appears to be another cron job starting with ac986, all marked as master-orchestrator agents.\n\nI need to verify the session labels against the actual data to make sure I'm reading the correct names and purposes. Once I confirm those details, I'll compile everything into a clean report to send to the Lead through the Telegram direct session.","thinkingSignature":"16ff80f5c79407a095ee2b8a11edf3e2b2936e71ca7f227ec82ec390f73a86df"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the active master-orchestrator sessions more closely:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_edosrzc4k7cl_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922","limit":3}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_edosrzc4k7cl_2","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","limit":3}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_edosrzc4k7cl_3","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bf